abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump was the ringleader of an effort to coerce Ukraine to dig up dirt on a domestic political rival, "worked hard" to cover it up and has shown no remorse, Democratic lawmakers said on Friday in his impeachment trial.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump was the ringleader of an effort to coerce Ukraine to dig up dirt on a domestic political rival, "worked hard" to cover it up and has shown no remorse, Democratic lawmakers said on Friday in his impeachment trial.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump was the ringleader of an effort to coerce Ukraine to dig up dirt on a domestic political rival, "worked hard" to cover it up and has shown no remorse, Democratic lawmakers said on Friday in his impeachment trial.
headline_main: Democrats Say Trump 'Worked Hard' on Ukraine Cover-Up, Shows No Remorse
headline_print_headline: Democrats Say Trump 'Worked Hard' on Ukraine Cover-Up, Shows No Remorse

abstract: U.S. Senate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer on Wednesday did not slam the door shut on the possibility of Joe Biden or his son Hunter testifying in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, but he said there was no need to hear from anyone unrelated to the charges.
snippet: U.S. Senate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer on Wednesday did not slam the door shut on the possibility of Joe Biden or his son Hunter testifying in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, but he said there was no need to hear from anyone ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer on Wednesday did not slam the door shut on the possibility of Joe Biden or his son Hunter testifying in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, but he said there was no need to hear from anyone unrelated to the charges.
headline_main: U.S. Sen. Schumer Says Bidens Have 'Nothing to Do' With Trump Impeachment Charges
headline_print_headline: U.S. Sen. Schumer Says Bidens Have 'Nothing to Do' With Trump Impeachment Charges

abstract: The U.S. television audience for Democrats' arguments that President Donald Trump should be impeached declined on Thursday to roughly 7.8 million viewers during live daytime coverage, according to data from the Nielsen ratings agency.
snippet: The U.S. television audience for Democrats' arguments that President Donald Trump should be impeached declined on Thursday to roughly 7.8 million viewers during live daytime coverage, according to data from the Nielsen ratings agency.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S. television audience for Democrats' arguments that President Donald Trump should be impeached declined on Thursday to roughly 7.8 million viewers during live daytime coverage, according to data from the Nielsen ratings agency.
headline_main: Trump Impeachment Trial's U.S. TV Audience Slips During Democrats' Arguments: Nielsen
headline_print_headline: Trump Impeachment Trial's U.S. TV Audience Slips During Democrats' Arguments: Nielsen

abstract: On the second day of House Democrats laying out their case in the U.S. Senate for removing President Donald Trump, there was little sign on Thursday that their arguments had changed any minds among Republican senators who control the chamber.
snippet: On the second day of House Democrats laying out their case in the U.S. Senate for removing President Donald Trump, there was little sign on Thursday that their arguments had changed any minds among Republican senators who control the chamber.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On the second day of House Democrats laying out their case in the U.S. Senate for removing President Donald Trump, there was little sign on Thursday that their arguments had changed any minds among Republican senators who control the chamber.
headline_main: Two Days Into Trump Trial, Republicans Appear Unmoved but Offer Democrats Some Praise
headline_print_headline: Two Days Into Trump Trial, Republicans Appear Unmoved but Offer Democrats Some Praise

abstract: Former Vice President Joe Biden leads other candidates for the Democratic presidential nomination, while several others appeared to be gaining momentum in their bid for the White House, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national opinion poll released on Thursday.
snippet: Former Vice President Joe Biden leads other candidates for the Democratic presidential nomination, while several others appeared to be gaining momentum in their bid for the White House, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national opinion poll released o...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Former Vice President Joe Biden leads other candidates for the Democratic presidential nomination, while several others appeared to be gaining momentum in their bid for the White House, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national opinion poll released on Thursday.
headline_main: Biden Leads, While Others Gain Momentum in Bid for 2020 Nomination, Poll Shows
headline_print_headline: Biden Leads, While Others Gain Momentum in Bid for 2020 Nomination, Poll Shows

abstract: The Iowa caucuses are more than a week away, but millions of Americans are already free to vote.
snippet: The Iowa caucuses are more than a week away, but millions of Americans are already free to vote.
lead_paragraph: SACRAMENTO, Calif. — The Iowa caucuses are more than a week away, but millions of Americans are already free to vote.
headline_main: Early Voting Means 2020 Primary Is Already Here for Millions
headline_print_headline: Early Voting Means 2020 Primary Is Already Here for Millions

abstract: As Joe Biden wrapped a bus tour of Iowa this week, the elderly crowd gathered at VFW Hall 7920 was a stark reminder of the former vice president's struggle to attract young people.
snippet: As Joe Biden wrapped a bus tour of Iowa this week, the elderly crowd gathered at VFW Hall 7920 was a stark reminder of the former vice president's struggle to attract young people.
lead_paragraph: OSAGE, Iowa — As Joe Biden wrapped a bus tour of Iowa this week, the elderly crowd gathered at VFW Hall 7920 was a stark reminder of the former vice president's struggle to attract young people.
headline_main: Democrats Struggle to Build Broad Support on Eve of Voting
headline_print_headline: Democrats Struggle to Build Broad Support on Eve of Voting
